1. RMM122  Suppose we laid out a very simple model of the Phillipines economy, roughly in line with Paul Krugman's argument.  Suppose the economy (in the 1980s) has two sectors labeled Manufacturing and Agriculture (which might here include harvesting garbage from 'Smokey Mountain.')

| Country | MPL           | wage in US\$  |
| ------- | ------------- | ------------- |
| USA:    | 30 widgets/hr | \$15 per hour |
| Mexico  | 3 widgets/hr  | \$4 per hour  |


